  <title>BeachStratCollectedShorelineData_Delivery_Version1</title>
  <abstract>This dataset includes updated shore armor mapping, updated historical shoretype mapping, updated drift cell mapping and naming, divergence zones, route information, HUC 10 and HUC 12 data, fetch, and erosion potential, all compatible with previous versions via the state ShoreZone Shoreline. 

This line feature class contains data updates applied as part of the ESRP grant-funded Beach Strategies project. All data are coincident with the state ShoreZone Shoreline (WDNR 2001). Updated historical shoretype mapping is a significant part of data updates; these data include results from the updated Historical Feeder Bluff Mapping effort by Coastal Geologic Services in 2017 for the Puget Sound Partnership. </abstract>
